Last updated: April 11, 2026

Our core promise
SmartTime collects only the minimum data needed to function. Your activity history never leaves your device. A small set of account and preference data is stored in the cloud so your settings follow you across devices.

1. What we collect
Activity data — stored locally only: Application name, process name, window title, session start and end time. Written to a SQLite database on your device at %APPDATA%\SmartTime\smarttime.db. This data is never uploaded.

Account data — stored in Firebase (cloud):

Email address
Display name
Profile photo URL (if set)
Account creation date
This data is used for authentication and account management only.

App category preferences — stored in Firebase (cloud): Your per-app category assignments (Productive / Neutral / Distracting) are saved to your account under users/{uid}/preferences/appCategories. This allows your productivity settings to persist across devices, reinstalls, and sign-outs. Only you can read or write your own category data.

App settings — stored locally: Refresh interval, idle threshold, debug mode, and other preferences are saved in %APPDATA%\SmartTime\settings.json on your device.

2. What we do NOT collect
The content of your documents, messages, or browser tabs
Screenshots or screen recordings
Keystrokes or mouse movements
Any data sent to third-party analytics or advertising services
3. Data sharing
We do not sell or share your data with any third party. The only external service used is Firebase (Google), which handles authentication and cloud preference storage. See the Firebase Privacy Policy.

4. Data deletion
You can delete all tracked session history at any time in Settings → Data & Privacy → Delete History. Deleting your account in Profile → Danger Zone removes your Firebase account and all associated cloud data including your category preferences.

5. Auto-updates
The App checks for updates by contacting GitHub Releases. This reveals your IP address to GitHub, but no activity data is transmitted.

6. Contact
Privacy concerns can be submitted via the GitHub issues page linked in the About tab.
